body:
It's the DSL implementation described in [Apache Beam: design of DSL SQL interface](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1uWXL_yF3UUO5GfCxbL6kWsmC8xCWfICU3RwiQKsk7Mk/edit?usp=sharing). 

It provides two methods `BeamSql.simpleQuery(...)` and `BeamSql.query(...)` to integrate SQL in Beam pipeline, by converting it into a `PTransform`, refer to `org.apache.beam.dsls.sql.example.BeamSqlExample` as a quick example.

Along with this DSL methods, some functions in the back-end are changed:
1. `BeamSqlRowCoder` is updated to have a input parameter `BeamSQLRecordType`, to declare row format, and it cannot be registered during initialization any more;
2. Interface in `BeamRelNode` is changed, to align with the goal, converting into PTransform;

The methods for CLI client are marked as `Experimental` in `BeamSql`, the difference is handled in `BeamIOSourceRel`, that whether an upstream PCollection is there, or need to generate from `BaseBeamTable`;
